# Setting up RUBE to use it with Calaveras
1. Symlink <rube_install_path>/config to <calaveras_path>/rube/config
2. On the Scripts panel click on the "script hooks setup dialog" and set the scripts folder to <calaveras_path>/rube/scripts, then link the "Images dropped" event with the calaverasResizeImage.rs file.

# Create a new level.
1. Run script to set custom properties <calavera_path>/rube/scripts/calaverasLevelCustomProperties.rs
2. Set Scene > Scene Settings > Custom Display > Property display filter script to <calavera_path>/rube/scripts/calaverasPropertyDisplayFilter.rs
3. Set Scene > Scene Settings > Custom Display > Label customization script to <calavera_path>/rube/scripts/calaverasLabelDisplay.rs
4. Set Scene > Scene Settings > Export Options > Specify Path to <calavera_path>/Resources/design.

# Create a new act.
1. Run script to set custom properties <calavera_path>/rube/scripts/calaverasActCustomProperties.rs
2. Set Scene > Scene Settings > Custom Display > Property display filter script to <calavera_path>/rube/scripts/calaverasPropertyDisplayFilter.rs
3. Set Scene > Scene Settings > Custom Display > Label customization script to <calavera_path>/rube/scripts/calaverasLabelDisplay.rs
4. Set Scene > Scene Settings > Export Options > Specify Path to <calavera_path>/Resources/design.

# After export to json
1. Run bash script to change files from .png to .pvr.

# Edition
t - Translate
s - Scale
r - Rotation
c - Set cursor

# Areas (go to edit vertices)
e - Add vertix to line
ee - Add free vertix to right
eee - Add free vertix to left
